President Obama met with President Zardari of Pakistan at the White House. The main topic of discussion was the shared efforts to fight terrorism and promote regional stability, with a focus on achieving a peaceful outcome in Afghanistan. President Obama emphasized the importance of the U.S.-Pakistan relationship and expressed continued support for Pakistan. He also mentioned that he is looking forward to visiting Pakistan later in the year. President Zardari will attend Ambassador Richard Holbrooke's memorial service at the Kennedy Center.